As a wine name, Chateau d’Yquem represents the ultimate — as Rolls-Royce and Caviar do in their respective classes. It is a rich, full, glorious and sweet wine from Sauternes. Normally it commands well over $7 the bottle — at this unbelievably low cost, we urge that you acquire some for your special dinner parties.

CORTON CHARLEMAGNE 1955 Estate Bottled, Chapuis

The white wines from the Corton Charlemagne vineyard are among the noblest of France, hard to come by, and can be classed with the great Montrachets.

BIENVENU, BATARD MONTRACHET, 1955 Estate Bottled, C. Ramonet

Mr. Ramonet recently satisfied his life long ambition by acquiring a small holding in the Batard Montrachet vine- yard. This is the first vintage obtained under his proprietor- ship. In our opnion, it is quite in the league with the best of the Montrachets.

FROM RHINE & MOSELLE

SCHARZHOFBERGER 1955 Estate Bottled, Egon Muller

The Scharzhof is a fine old manor house owned for gen- erations by the Muller family. Superb Saar wine and one of the great dry white wines of.the world.

PIESPORTER GOLDTROPFCHEN SPATLESE 1953

Estate Bottled, Kesselstatt Cellars

Astonishing stature, magnificent fullness, and all of the flowery-like delicacy of a great 1953. Spatlese from Moselle. Competes with Moselles that command $6 the bottle.
